(- Each listed action is one complete simplified turn: sow + selected duty/tithe ) Tj
T*
(resolution.) Tj
T*
(- Prints a numbered list of readable full-turn summaries.) Tj
T*
(- Prints a final legal-action count.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why this matters:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- It is one of the fastest ways to debug action generation.) Tj
T*
(- It should usually be checked before trusting solver output.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Example output:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Legal actions for scenario 'mancala_sandbox_001':) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Turn: sow city -> north -> north_east -> east | selected duty: north | action: produce) Tj
T*
(2. Turn: sow city -> north -> north_east -> east | selected duty: north | action: tithe) Tj
T*
(...) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Total legal actions: N) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Command 3: Run the simple solver) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(python3 -m pilgrim.cli solve scenarios/mancala_sandbox_001.json --depth 3) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(What it does right now:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Runs the current exact-search prototype.) Tj
T*
(- Searches to the specified depth in **full turns** \(`--depth 3` means 3 complete turns\).) Tj
T*
(- Uses a temporary placeholder evaluation function.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Example output:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Solve result for scenario 'mancala_sandbox_001') Tj
T*
(Depth: 3) Tj
T*
(Best score: 3) Tj
T*
(Nodes expanded: 27) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Best first full turn:) Tj
T*
(Turn: sow city -> north -> north_east -> east | selected duty: east | action: ) Tj
T*
(clerical_silversmith) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Best line:) Tj
T*
(1. Turn: sow city -> north -> north_east -> east | selected duty: east | action: ) Tj
T*
(clerical_silversmith) Tj
T*
(2. Turn: sow north -> north_east | selected duty: north_east | action: clerical_devotion) Tj
T*
(3. Turn: sow city -> south | selected duty: south | action: tithe) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(How to interpret the current output) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- The old machine-oriented token `best_action=sow:0:1->2->3` is now shown in readable ) Tj
ET
