(form.) Tj
T*
(- `city -> north -> north_east -> east` corresponds to position IDs `0 -> 1 -> 2 -> 3`.) Tj
T*
(- `nodes_expanded` means the number of search nodes explored.) Tj
T*
(- `best_score` is still a value under a **temporary placeholder sandbox evaluation**, not ) Tj
T*
(true final Pilgrim VP.) Tj
T*
(- `best line` is now a sequence of full turns, not alternating sow/resolve sub-actions.) Tj
T*
(- Together, this confirms the current development loop works end-to-end:) Tj
T*
(  `scenario -> validate -> legal actions -> search -> recommendation`.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Using `--verbose` with `solve` prints:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- all transition events for the recommended first full turn \(sowing + duty/tithe + ) Tj
T*
(invariants\)) Tj
T*
(- a compact state summary after applying that first full turn) Tj
T*
(- `Acted player` \(the player who executed that recommended turn\)) Tj
T*
(- `Next active player` \(the player whose turn is next\)) Tj
T*
(- the acted player state so resource gains and acolyte recall are directly visible) Tj
T*
(- `Piety position` and `Piety track VP` for direct track-value inspection) Tj
T*
(- an evaluation breakdown for the acted player after the first full turn) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Position mapping used by the current sandbox:) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- `0 = city`) Tj
T*
(- `1 = north`) Tj
T*
(- `2 = north_east`) Tj
T*
(- `3 = east`) Tj
T*
(- `4 = south_east`) Tj
T*
(- `5 = south`) Tj
T*
(- `6 = south_west`) Tj
T*
(- `7 = west`) Tj
T*
(- `8 = north_west`) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(What this does not mean yet) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- The engine is not complete for full Pilgrim gameplay.) Tj
T*
(- The solver score is not final-game scoring quality.) Tj
T*
(- This is not strategic proof or balance validation.) Tj
T*
(- Only the current deterministic mancala-sandbox slice is covered.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Piety Track Scoring \(v0.2\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(- Piety is now treated as a capped track position \(`max_position = 12`\).) Tj
T*
(- Piety position and piety VP are different values.) Tj
T*
(- The VP lookup table is loaded from `configs/piety.json`.) Tj
T*
(- Sandbox solver evaluation is still temporary, but now uses **piety track VP** instead of) Tj
T*
( raw piety position.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Typical development workflow) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(1. Edit rules/config/scenario files.) Tj
ET
